"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-olympics-news-swimming-world-championships-2024-doha\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The first world swimming championships to be held in an Olympic year begin Sunday in Doha and air daily live onPeacock.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 119, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 85, \"end\": 89, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3773712651604897e-20, \"text\": \"Doha\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Doha\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most nations sent smaller teams than usual given many swimmers are training for Olympic Trials.\", \"from\": 121, \"to\": 216, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For the U.S., many are also in the middle of the NCAA season.\", \"from\": 217, \"to\": 278, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. roster of 20 is led by Kate Douglass, who won six medals at the 2023 World Championships, and Carson Foster, who won three individual medals between the 2022 and 2023 Worlds.\", \"from\": 280, \"to\": 463, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 312, \"end\": 325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\"}, {\"begin\": 383, \"end\": 396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carson_Foster\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carson Foster\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carson_Foster\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carson_Foster\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Internationally, headliners include Swede Sarah Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m (a record 21-time individual world medalist), Brits Adam Peaty, Tom Dean and Duncan Scott, Japan's Daiya Seto, Lithuanian Ruta Meilutyte and Tunisian Ahmed Hafnaoui.\", \"from\": 465, \"to\": 687, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 507, \"end\": 521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m\", \"score\": 0.9999994657338511, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sarah Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m\"}, {\"begin\": 574, \"end\": 584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}, {\"begin\": 586, \"end\": 594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Dean_(swimmer)\", \"score\": 0.9999936593363623, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Dean\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Dean_(swimmer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Dean_(swimmer)\"}, {\"begin\": 599, \"end\": 611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duncan_Scott_(swimmer)\", \"score\": 0.9913273362707572, \"rank\": 0.004373974849644039, \"text\": \"Duncan Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duncan_Scott_(swimmer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duncan_Scott_(swimmer)\"}, {\"begin\": 613, \"end\": 618, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8060826498859035, \"rank\": 0.19406532073742574, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\"