es three times, which is rarely done.\", \"from\": 689, \"to\": 905, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 737, \"end\": 745, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\", \"score\": 0.9652346553762287, \"rank\": 0.03601750561919571, \"text\": \"Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She could scratch out of races.\", \"from\": 906, \"to\": 937, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"USA Swimming will not enter a women's 4x100m free relay but plans to enter later relays that Douglass could be a part of.\", \"from\": 939, \"to\": 1060, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 939, \"end\": 951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USA Swimming\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\"}, {\"begin\": 1032, \"end\": 1040, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\", \"score\": 0.9652346553762287, \"rank\": 0.03601750561919571, \"text\": \"Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her preliminary individual lineup: 50m and 100m freestyles, 100m and 200m breaststrokes, 50m butterfly and 200m individual medley.\", \"from\": 1062, \"to\": 1192, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She is the reigning world champ in the 200m IM and reigning U.S. champion in the 100m free.\", \"from\": 1194, \"to\": 1285, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1254, \"end\": 1258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999555033416734, \"rank\": 3.512611083748645e-05, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In January, she broke the American record in the 200m breast.\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1347, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1312, \"end\": 1320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9985827870264895, \"rank\": 0.0013602258795807655, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"MORE:Douglass took different strokes to swim success  Simone Manuel owns the female record of seven medals at one world championships (2019).\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 1490, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1354, \"end\": 1362, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\", \"score\": 0.9652346553762287, \"rank\": 0.03601750561919571, \"text\": \"Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stu_Douglass\"}, {\"begin\": 1403, \"end\": 1416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Manuel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Manuel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Manuel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Manuel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Missy Franklin owns the female record of six gold medals at one worlds (2013).\", \"from\": 1491, \"to\": 1569, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1491, \"end\": 1496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missy_Elliott\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1192576780339814e-13, \"text\": \"Missy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missy_Elliott\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missy_Elliott\"}, {\"begin\": 1497, \"end\": 1505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benjamin_Franklin\", \"score\": 0.999997491472604, \"rank\": 2.508533665115147e-06, \"text\": \"Franklin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benjamin_Franklin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benjamin_Franklin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peaty, the world record holder and two-time Olympic gold medalist in the men's 100m breast, competes at his first global championship since the Tokyo Games.\", \"from\": 1571, \"to\": 1727, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 29-year-old missed worlds in 2022 (fractured bone in his foot) and 2023 (did not enter trials, citing mental health).\", \"from\": 1729, \"to\": 1850, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Peaty's absence last July, China's Qin Haiyang won the world title in 57.69 seconds to become the second-fastest man in history.\", \"from\": 1852, \"to\": 1983, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1882, \"end\": 1887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9481543703066354, \"rank\": 0.05434795088286111, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1890, \"end\": 1901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_Haiyang\", \"score\": 0.9999938624998401, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Qin Haiyang\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_Haiyang\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_Haiyang\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Qin is not competing at these worlds.\", \"from\": 1984, \"to\": 2021, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1984, \"end\": 1987, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_dynasty\", \"score\": 0.9343431695047866, \"rank\": 0.053896174806834306, \"text\": \"Qin\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_dynasty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_dynasty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peaty owns the top 14 times ever, led by his world record of 56.88.\", \"from\": 2023, \"to\": 2090, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His best time in limited action since Tokyo is 58.88.\", \"from\": 2091, \"to\": 2144, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2129, \"end\": 2134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.5747389525059564, \"rank\": 0.7399203510364744, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If the 30-year-old Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m earns a medal in all three of her individual events (50m and 100m butterflies, 50m freestyle), plus a relay medal, she will tie the absent Katie Ledecky's female record 26 career world medals.\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2366, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2313, \"end\": 2326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last year, Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m broke her tie with Michael Phelps for the most medals in individual events only.\", \"from\": 2368, \"to\": 2468, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2407, \"end\": 2421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4006143953509646e-62, \"text\": \"Michael Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A Division ofNBCUniversal.\", \"from\": 2470, \"to\": 2496, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2470, \"end\": 2480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_Footbal